latestPosts.caption: And just like that, our baby bird is leaving the nest and flying off to Symbiosis Hyderabad for Law. Watching you grow into this fierce, brilliant, beautiful young woman has been our life’s greatest joy. As you head off to college, our hearts are bursting with pride… and just a little bit breaking too. Go chase your dreams, baby sis — the world is lucky to have you. #BittersweetGoodbye #OffToCollege #forevermybaby

latestPosts.caption:
Five years ago, Shoumili took her first graceful step into the world of Bharatnatyam under the guidance of her incredible guru @shreyasigopinath and @the_dance_atelier .... What followed was a journey of discipline, devotion, and deep cultural connection.
The second edition of Sadhana wasn’t just a performance—it was a celebration. A moment to pause, reflect, and soak in the richness of India’s classical dance heritage. From expressive abhinaya to powerful rhythms, the stage came alive with stories that words could never tell.
Here's to Shoumili, her guru, and every dancer keeping our traditions alive—one performance at a time. 
#IndianClassicalDance #bharatnatyamlegacy #classicaldance #bharatnatyam

It took a decade to visit Kolkata again, but what a revelation it has been... a ceremony to celebrate the youngest scion of the Banerjee clan, non-stop adda with cousins, great heritage food and old world cocktails - all perfectly encased in the steaming weather of City of Joy... it was four days to remember with @shhhh_shiv @sunnibanerjee.on @papiya.banerjee.754 @lsaibal @ishitabanerjee197 @krishaislost, and many more... #famjam #familytime❤️
Holi 2025 was a destination celebration... one that we had planned with the tigers. Though we couldn't spot one, but the adventure and pool time was one to remember ❤️❤️❤️

latestPosts.caption: 13 years ago, I reviewed the first @cafedelhiheights during my stint as the Food Editor of Good Housekeeping. Today, being a part of their 13th birthday celebrations at their new Ikigai concept restaurant, I realised that I had never been away. The people are the same - warm, loving and welcoming. Thank you @kavita.devgan for inviting me to this splendid occasion; @shammibatra for the wonderful hospitality; and @vetaratra for being my superwoman muse. It was an evening to remember.
